full_text: Copied at the National Archives at Kansas City gw FL10-621 Formerly AdS-367 (12-20-55) 134-427 U. S. DEPARTMENT OF COMMERCE BUREAU OF THE CENSUS WASHINGTON 25, D. C. Jacob Lavine The September 5, 1957 Re: 630 Division St. Trenton 10, N. J. The following information, including spelling of name, relationship, age, etc. , is an EXACT COPY of the census record as reported by the census taker on the original schedule. Census of 1920 taken as of January 1 , 630 Division, Trenton County Mercer State New Jersey Name Relationship Age Place of birth Citizenship Lavine, Jacob Head 1019 35 Russia *Naturalized - Freda Wife and family *Year of immigration 1893 The name of the person for whom the search was requested was not found listed in the area given during the Census 1900 Robert-W Biligins ROBERT W/ BURGESS Bureau of the Census The above information is furnished upon application with the understanding that in no case shall the information furnished be used to the detriment of the person or persons to whom the information relates, in accordance with Title 13, United States Code, Section 8. The Bureau of the Census does not issue birth certificates, but this record is often accepted in place of one. U. S. GOVERNMENT PRINTING OFFICE 1956-O-370688
